        "content": "What is OS Command Injection?"
      },
      {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "[Textbook] OS command injection, also known as shell injection, is a web security vulnerability that allows an attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the host operating system (OS) of a server running a vulnerable application. This type of vulnerability can lead to a full compromise of the application and its data."
